{
  "uid": "t212",
  "root_name": "出曜經 (T 212)",
  "translated_name": "The Appearance of Light ",
  "node_type": "branch",
  "blurb": "The Indian original text compiled by Dharmatrāta 法救 consisted of 33 chapters and about 1000 verses, and it was translated by Saṁghabhadra 僧伽跋澄 and Zhu Fonian 竺佛念 during 398–399. The present T 212 has 34 chapters, and its chapters correspond to the present Udānavarga, which has 33 chapters and 1050 verses, except that it has two separated chapters, i.e. the chapter of non-carelessness 無放逸品 and the chapter of carelessness 放逸品, for the chapter 'Apramādavarga' of the Udānavarga. Like T 211, this text also provides the verses along with the background stories in prose. When the verses are same with those of T 210, the translators of T 211 followed the translation of T 210 rather than did a new translation.",
  "acronym": "Lzh Dhp 3",
  "root_lang_iso": "lzh",
  "root_lang_name": "Chinese",
